There is probably some path problem. Try this:

Start an interactive python session by typing &quot;python&quot; or &quot;pythonw&quot;. 
 From the Python prompt, type:

from MixMaster import MixMaster
MixMaster()

This should launch MixMaster.  But if there is some installation 
problem on your system, it will at least let you read the error message 
without the window disappearinig.  Once you fix the problem, running 
MixMaster from the Start menu should work too.

